theorem
Th25: (for X being RealLinearSpace holds (for M,N being (Subset of X) holds (for v being (Point of X) holds (( v + M ) meets N iff v in ( N + ( - M ) )))))
proof
let X being RealLinearSpace;
let M being (Subset of X),N being (Subset of X);
let v being (Point of X);
A1: ( N + ( ( - 1 ) * M ) ) = { ( u + w ) where u is (Point of X),w is (Point of X): (u in N & w in ( ( - 1 ) * M )) } by RUSUB_4:def 9;
hereby
A2: ( v + M ) = { ( v + u ) where u is (Point of X): u in M } by RUSUB_4:def 8;
assume ( v + M ) meets N;
then consider z being set such that A3: z in ( v + M ) and A4: z in N by XBOOLE_0:3;
consider u being (Point of X) such that A5: ( v + u ) = z and A6: u in M by A3,A2;
reconsider z as (Point of X) by A3;
A7: ( ( - 1 ) * u ) in ( ( - 1 ) * M ) by A6;
( z + ( ( - 1 ) * u ) ) = ( v + ( u + ( ( - 1 ) * u ) ) ) by A5,RLVECT_1:def 3
.= ( v + ( u + ( - u ) ) ) by RLVECT_1:16
.= ( v + ( 0. X ) ) by RLVECT_1:5
.= v by RLVECT_1:4;
hence v in ( N + ( - M ) ) by A4,A7,CKB4:1;
end;
assume v in ( N + ( - M ) );
then consider u being (Point of X),w being (Point of X) such that A8: v = ( u + w ) and A9: u in N and A10: w in ( ( - 1 ) * M ) by A1;
consider w9 being (Point of X) such that A11: w = ( ( - 1 ) * w9 ) and A12: w9 in M by A10;
A13: ( ( - 1 ) * w ) = ( ( ( - 1 ) * ( - 1 ) ) * w9 ) by A11,RLVECT_1:def 7
.= w9 by RLVECT_1:def 8;
( v + w9 ) = ( u + ( w + w9 ) ) by A8,RLVECT_1:def 3
.= ( u + ( w + ( - w ) ) ) by A13,RLVECT_1:16
.= ( u + ( 0. X ) ) by RLVECT_1:5
.= u by RLVECT_1:4;
then u in ( v + M ) by A12,CKB5:1;
hence thesis by A9,XBOOLE_0:3;
end;
